event_investment_decisions.event_description:
The FED interest rates are defined in this market by the upper bound of the target federal funds range. The decisions on the target federal fund range are made by the Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) meetings.

This market will resolve to the amount of basis points the upper bound of the target federal funds rate is changed by versus the level it was prior to the Federal Reserve's October 2025 meeting.

If the target federal funds rate is changed to a level not expressed in the displayed options, the change will be rounded up to the nearest 25 and will resolve to the relevant bracket. (e.g. if there's a cut/increase of 12.5 bps it will be considered to be 25 bps)

The resolution source for this market is the FOMC’s statement after its meeting scheduled for October 28 - 29, 2025 according to the official calendar: https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/fomccalendars.htm.

The level and change of the target federal funds rate is also published at the official website of the Federal Reserve at https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/openmarket.htm.

This market may resolve as soon as the FOMC’s statement for their October meeting with relevant data is issued. If no statement is released by the end date of the next scheduled meeting, this market will resolve to the "No change" bracket.

decision.rationale: The Federal Reserve just cut rates by 25 basis points in September 2025 and signaled a gradual approach to further cuts, with projections showing two more cuts for the remainder of 2025. A 50+ basis point cut in October would be unusually aggressive given this cautious approach. The market is pricing this at 7.35%, which seems high given the Fed's recent communication about gradual cuts. I'm estimating the true probability at 3%.

market_investment_decisions.market_question: Fed decreases interest rates by 50+ bps after October 2025 meeting?

decision.rationale: The Federal Reserve just cut rates by 25 basis points in September and has signaled more cuts are likely, with projections showing two more cuts for 2025. Given this context, another 25 basis point cut in October seems most probable. However, the market price of 78.5% seems somewhat high given that the Fed has only projected two more cuts for the entire remainder of the year. I estimate the true probability at 65%.

market_investment_decisions.market_question: Fed decreases interest rates by 25 bps after October 2025 meeting?

decision.rationale: Although the Federal Reserve has signaled more rate cuts are likely after their September 25 basis point reduction, there is still a possibility they might pause in October to assess the impact of their recent actions. The market is pricing this at only 14.5%, which seems quite low given that the Fed has only projected two more cuts for the remainder of 2025, suggesting they might space them out. I estimate the true probability at 25%.

market_investment_decisions.market_question: No change in Fed interest rates after October 2025 meeting?

decision.rationale: The Federal Reserve is clearly in a rate-cutting cycle, having just implemented a 25 basis point cut in September 2025 and signaling more cuts to come. With inflation trends and economic indicators pointing toward continued easing, a rate increase in October is virtually impossible. The market is pricing this at 0.75%, which still seems high for such an unlikely event. I estimate the true probability at 0.1%.
